				<p><p>You may have misread (or else your book misrepresented) the definition odometry; it is not a direct measurement of position, just distance travelled.  Odometry may say that you travelled a mile, but whether you ended up a mile away or right back where you started will depend on other aspects of your movement.</p>

<p>By combining odometry with other measurements, the process of estimating your position -- "dead reckoning" -- becomes more accurate.</p>
